cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the development and evaluation of predictive models for clinical data, which involves machine learning techniques and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which deals with the application of computational methods to solve problems in various fields, including healthcare. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB) to handle the large volume of clinical data. Finally, the paper has implications for healthcare (cs.HC) by highlighting the need for data sharing among hospitals to improve model performance.
